Class App

java.lang.Object
edu.touro.mco152.bm.App
public class App extends Object
Primary class for global variables, main and common methods for the badbm application.

This class serves as the entry point for the application and manages global configurations, application state, and initialization of the GUI components. It also provides utility methods for loading and saving configuration settings, managing benchmark states, and handling disk operations.

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Starts the badbm application.

      Parses the command line arguments and initiates the benchmarking process by delegating the various tasks to the appropriate class.

      Parameters:
      args - the command line arguments passed to the application.

    • getVersion

      public static String getVersion()
      Retrieves the application version from the build properties.

      If the version is not found, or the file is not readable the method defaults to return "0.0".

      Returns:
      the application version as a String or "0.0" if the version is not found.
